column1: '''Oxford University visitor's page''' refers to a sheet (8" x 9.5") removed from a visitor's book at the [[University of Oxford]], stamped [[20 October]] [[1911]]. The page features signatures of Oxford University undergraduates, and the names of their respective colleges. [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] added his signature about three quarters of the way down the page, and wrote his college, "[[University of Oxford#Exeter College
column5: articlename=JRR TOLKIEN Extremely Rare Signed Oxford University Visitor's Autograph Page (Item number: 110928410792)
